								<h3>
										<a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news_category/national/" class="category-link">National</a>				</h3>
				<p>
					<a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/06/04/national/japan-softens-re-entry-ban-foreign-residents/">Japan softens re-entry ban that left foreign residents stranded</a>
				</p>
									<h5 class="writer" role="author">by <a href="https://www.japantimes.co.jp/author/int-magdalena_osumi/" title="Posts by Magdalena Osumi" class="author url fn" rel="nofollow">Magdalena Osumi</a></h5>
							</hgroup>
		</header>
		<p>
			The government says it has softened its stance on humanitarian grounds and will now allow foreign residents to re-enter the country regardless of their visa status.<br />
			<time datetime="2020-06-04T18:47:22+09:00" pubdate>
				<div class="margin-5-0"></div>			</time>
		</p>
	</article>
